  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Monday. School held Career Day today, where different adults from the neighborhood came in to talk about their jobs.",
      "zh": "星期一。今天學校辦了職業日，附近社區不同的大人來學校講他們的工作。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The idea is that we are supposed to leave with some idea of what we want to be when we grow up.",
      "zh": "這個活動的用意是，我們離開的時候應該對長大想做什麼多少有點想法。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I left with twelve completely different, equally confusing ideas, which I am told is a very normal outcome for a thirteen-year-old.",
      "zh": "我離開的時候有十二個完全不同、同樣讓人困惑的想法，聽說對一個十三歲的孩子來說，這是很正常的結果。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The first booth belonged to a local fisherman, who told us stories about waking up before sunrise to check his nets.",
      "zh": "第一個攤位是一位當地漁夫，他跟我們講了他天還沒亮就起床檢查漁網的故事。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Being a fisherman is not romantic every day,\" he admitted. \"Some mornings the ocean gives you nothing at all.\"",
      "zh": "「當漁夫並不是每天都浪漫，」他坦承：「有些早晨，大海什麼都不給你。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Next was a sailor who had traveled to more countries than I could name, describing life on a huge cargo ship.",
      "zh": "接下來是一位水手，他去過的國家比我能講出來的還多，他描述了在一艘巨大貨輪上的生活。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice asked if being a sailor gets lonely, and he said yes, but the ocean at night makes up for a lot of that loneliness.",
      "zh": "Bernice 問當水手會不會孤單，他說會，但夜晚的大海會彌補很多那種孤單感。"
    },
    {
      "en": "A local gardener showed us photos of a public park she had shaped over twenty years, one flower bed at a time.",
      "zh": "一位當地的園丁給我們看她花了二十年、一床花壇一床花壇整理出來的公園照片。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"People walk through my work every day and never know my name,\" she said. \"That is fine. The garden remembers.\"",
      "zh": "「人們每天走過我的作品，卻從來不知道我的名字，」她說：「這樣也好，花園記得就夠了。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "A friendly barber demonstrated how he cuts hair while somehow also managing a shop full of chatting customers at the same time.",
      "zh": "一位親切的理髮師示範他怎麼一邊剪頭髮，一邊還能同時應付一整間客人聊個不停的店。"
    },
    {
      "en": "A shopkeeper who runs the little store near our school explained how she orders products, manages a small budget, and still finds time to remember every regular customer's favorite snack.",
      "zh": "在我們學校附近開小店的一位店主，解釋她怎麼進貨、管理有限的預算，還能記得每位常客最愛的零食。"
    },
    {
      "en": "A businessman in a very sharp suit talked about managing a whole company, being both an employer and, once, a very nervous employee himself.",
      "zh": "一位穿著非常筆挺西裝的商人，講述他管理整間公司的經歷，他既是雇主，也曾經是一位非常緊張的員工。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"A good manager remembers what it felt like to be a new employee,\" he said. \"I try not to forget that feeling.\"",
      "zh": "「一位好的主管會記得自己剛當員工時的感覺，」他說：「我試著不去忘記那種感覺。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "A salesperson explained that the hardest part of her job is not selling things, it is listening carefully to what people actually need.",
      "zh": "一位銷售員解釋，她工作最難的部分不是賣東西，而是仔細聽出人們真正需要的是什麼。"
    },
    {
      "en": "A waiter from a busy restaurant downtown talked about carrying six plates at once without ever mixing up a single order.",
      "zh": "市區一間忙碌餐廳的服務生，講述他怎麼一次端六個盤子，卻從來不會搞錯任何一份訂單。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Being a good host matters just as much as good food,\" he said. \"People remember how you made them feel.\"",
      "zh": "「當一位好的接待者，跟食物好吃一樣重要，」他說：「人們會記得你讓他們有什麼感覺。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "A police officer talked about long night shifts and how much of the job is actually just being a calm, steady presence for people in trouble.",
      "zh": "一位警官談到漫長的夜班，以及這份工作有多少時候其實只是在人們遇到麻煩時，當一個冷靜、穩定的存在。"
    },
    {
